Ad Text:
Full time, 3-year fixed term opportunity to fast track your career as an Automation Graduate within the University's Automation & Innovation Team starting July 2026
Seeking graduate students (completing studies in Semester 1 of 2026), Gain invaluable professional experience from our structured three-year graduate program
Base Salary $83,038 + 17% superannuation



Join the Innovation Revolution: Unleash Your Potential as an Automation Graduate!



Are you a bright and enthusiastic software engineering university graduate or final-year student from the University of Sydney? If so, brace yourself for the opportunity of a lifetime!



The University of Sydney's 2026 Graduate Program Automation Stream is calling for talented individuals to join our cutting-edge Automation & Innovation Hub (AI Hub). The AI Hub's services include robotic process automation (virtual robots that perform complex tasks on a computer), chatbots, dashboards and other bespoke programs leveraging AI and Machine Learning components.



As a key member of our AI Hub, you'll play an integral role in designing and deploying software solutions that will elevate the University experience for students and staff alike. Get hands-on with a diverse array of exciting technologies such as:


BluePrism (Robotic Process Automation)
Python-based automation
Google Cloud
Microsoft Azure



As you grow and gain valuable experience, you'll have the opportunity to tackle complex innovation projects, integrating cutting-edge tech like Generative AI, Natural Language Processing, Machine Learning, Time Series Forecasting, and Optical Character Recognition (OCR).



At the AI Hub, we're invested in your growth and success. Enjoy an array of career boosting opportunities, including fully-funded training, mentorship programs, and coaching sessions. Gain industry-recognized certifications and build a solid foundation for a prosperous career in the tech industry.

Through our consulting nature, you'll rapidly expand your horizons by collaborating with various operational areas of the University. Empower them with bespoke solutions to their unique challenges and witness the real impact of your work.



Join an award-winning Graduate Program that takes pride in nurturing exceptional talents like you. Develop transferable skills that will set you apart in the industry, while building lasting connections with top professionals. Learn and develop with a cross functional graduate cohort with fun social programs and networking events.



This is your chance to shine and shape the future of automation! Apply now to seize this exhilarating opportunity and make your mark at the University of Sydney's Automation & Innovation Hub!





Responsibilities


deliver automation solutions in an agile team
build relationships with stakeholders and manage project communications
troubleshoot and fix issues in automated processes
identify and implement process improvements.



Benefits


fully funded training and industry-recognised certifications
mentoring and support throughout the program
opportunity to gain transferable skills, with exposure to various technologies and platforms such as:
Generative AI
Natural language processing
Machine learning
Optical character recognition (OCR)
Microsoft Azure and Google Cloud
Blue Prism
competitive salary and access to various career acceleration programs
fun and collaborative work culture with social programs
hybrid work options available.



Eligibility


recent graduate or final-year student (completing studies by end of Semester 1, 2026) from the University of Sydney
strong academic performance (Credit average minimum)
relevant working rights for full time employment in Australia.



Minimum Qualifications


Undergraduate degree in Computer Science, Software Development, Software Engineering, Computing, Information Technology, relevant technical field, or equivalent practical experience
experience with any of the following programming languages: Python, C++, C# or Java
ability to communicate effectively.



Preferred Qualifications


experience with browser-based automation such as Selenium
strong programming skills
experience with robotic process automation (RPA) tools such as Blue Prism, UiPath and Robocorp.


Work Rights
You must have unrestricted work rights in Australia for the duration of this employment to apply. Visa sponsorship is not available for this appointment.

Pre-employment checks

Your employment is conditional upon the completion of all role required pre-employment or background checks in terms satisfactory to the University. Similarly, your ongoing employment is conditional upon the satisfactory maintenance of all relevant clearances and background check requirements. If you do not meet these conditions, the University may take any necessary step, including the termination of your employment.

At the University of Sydney, our shared values include diversity and inclusion and we strive to be a place where everyone can thrive. Applications (including a cover letter, CV, and any additional supporting documentation) can be submitted via the Apply button at the top of the page.

We are seeking an experienced AI & Innovation Engineer to join our Technology Delivery team supporting a strategic AI-powered system.

This role plays a critical part in ensuring the quality, reliability, and performance of modern Machine Learning, Large Language Model (LLM), and Generative AI solutions. You will design and implement scalable automation frameworks across the full technology stack - from React-based user interfaces through to backend services, AI models, search platforms, and data orchestration pipelines.

You will lead testing innovation for AI-driven applications, validating contextual accuracy, factual correctness, and ongoing performance of LLM models while enabling continuous delivery of platform enhancements.

Key Responsibilities

Design and implement enterprise-grade test automation frameworks across UI, API, backend, and AI services

Develop automated testing strategies for ML, LLM, and Generative AI applications

Validate AI outputs for accuracy, relevance, and response quality across multiple models

Integrate automation into CI/CD pipelines to support continuous delivery

Build end-to-end regression and performance test suites

Monitor automation metrics and provide actionable quality insights

Lead test planning, coverage strategy, and risk-based testing activities

Mentor junior engineers and promote automation best practices

Collaborate closely with developers, product teams, and stakeholders

Drive continuous improvement of testing frameworks and DevOps practices

Technical Environment

Languages & Tools: Python, pytest, FastAPI

Automation: Playwright, Selenium, Appium, REST Assured

AI & Data: Azure OpenAI, AWS Bedrock, Databricks, Elasticsearch, Vector Search

Frontend & Backend: React / Next.js, APIs, distributed services

Cloud & DevOps: AWS, Azure, Git, CI/CD pipelines

Skills & Experience

Strong experience designing scalable test automation frameworks

Hands-on testing of AI, NLP, or LLM-based applications

Advanced Python automation development

Experience testing complex distributed systems, APIs, and data platforms

Deep understanding of Agile delivery and DevOps practices

Experience with cloud-based testing environments

Ability to produce meaningful quality metrics and reporting

What You'll Bring

Technical leadership in automation and quality engineering

Strong analytical and problem-solving capability

Passion for emerging AI technologies and innovation

Ability to work autonomously while contributing to high-performing teams

Desirable Certifications

ISTQB Advanced Test Automation Engineering (CTAL-TAE)

AI/ML or Data Science certifications

Python or SQL certifications

Why Join Us?

This is an opportunity to work at the forefront of AI and Generative AI technology, shaping testing practices for next-generation intelligent platforms while delivering meaningful enterprise impact.
